<law><law_id>674</law_id><section_number>12-2105</section_number><catch_line>RECORD KEEPING REQUIREMENTS.</catch_line><history/><order_by>12-2105</order_by><metadata/><url>/12-2105/</url><token>12-2105</token><structure><unit label="division" level="1" identifier="II">Division II - Planning and Development</unit><unit label="part" level="3" identifier="12">PART 12 - LICENSING AND REGULATION</unit><unit label="chapter" level="4" identifier="2">CHAPTER 2. - BUSINESSES AND TRADES</unit><unit label="article" level="2" identifier="C">ARTICLE C. - PAWNBROKERS [3]</unit></structure><referred_to_by><reference>12-2106</reference></referred_to_by><text><section id="1940" prefix="(a)"><text>Every pawnbroker shall keep consecutively numbered records of each pawn transaction. The records shall correspond in all essential particulars to a detachable pawn ticket or copy thereof attached to the record.</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(a)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(a)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(a)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1941" prefix="(b)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1942" prefix="(1)"><text>	A clear and accurate description of the property, including model and serial number if indicated on the property. 
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(1)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(1)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(1)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1943" prefix="(2)"><text>	The name, residence address, phone number, and date of birth of the pledgor. 
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(2)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(2)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(2)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1944" prefix="(3)"><text>	The date of the transaction.
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(3)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(3)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(3)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1945" prefix="(4)"><text>	The type of identification and identification number accepted from pledgor.
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(4)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(4)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(4)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1946" prefix="(5)"><text>	Physical description of the pledgor.
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(5)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(5)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(5)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1947" prefix="(6)"><text>	The amount of money advanced.
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(6)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(6)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(6)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1948" prefix="(7)"><text>	The date and the amount due.
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(7)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(7)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(7)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1949" prefix="(8)"><text>	All monthly pawn charges, including interest, annual percentage rate on interest, and total recovery fee. 
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(8)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(8)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(8)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1950" prefix="(9)"><text>	Agreed upon stated value between the pledgor and the pawnbroker in case of loss or destruction of pledged item. Unless otherwise noted the stated value is the same as the loan value. 
</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section><section>(9)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)(9)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)(9)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1951" prefix="(c)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1952" prefix="(1)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section><section>(1)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)(1)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)(1)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1953" prefix="(2)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section><section>(2)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)(2)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)(2)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1954" prefix="(3)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section><section>(3)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)(3)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)(3)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1955" prefix="(4)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section><section>(4)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)(4)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)(4)</prefix_anchor><level>2</level></section><section id="1956" prefix="(d)"><text>The pledgor shall sign the pawn ticket and shall receive an exact copy of the pawn ticket, which shall be signed or initialed by the pawnbroker or an employee of the pawnbroker. These records shall be available for inspection each regular workday by the Police Department. The records shall be provided to the Police Department within twenty-four (24) hours after the record is created in one of the following ways: 
1.	Hand delivery to: 110 South McDowell Street
Raleigh Police Department 4th floor
Attention: pawnshop investigator
2.	Facsimile to: (919) 890-3004 Attention: pawnshop investigator
3.	Electronic data as set forth in the next paragraph.
All pawnbrokers are required to utilize a reporting system that offers an electronic data transmission system that is compatible with the standard used by the local City or County law enforcement computer system. The electronic data must be provided to the appropriate law enforcement agency as designated by the Raleigh Police Department within twenty-four (24) hours after the record is created.</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(d)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(d)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(d)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1957" prefix="(e)"><text/><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(e)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(e)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(e)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section></text></law>
